other god's version of Do I sound broken to you I don't You point out that your mother's treatment upset you and see inconsistencies in various I'm not sure if that constitutes broken ness or It certainly consititutes I don't see how disillusionment enters into You see I presented my mother's treatment of me to show the cause of my questioning my atheism a questioning which continues to this I had already been an atheist for five years before having any contact with my mother's version of If anything I had become somewhat disillusioned with atheism uh oh I thought What if there is a God Yes in a way I have also become disillusioned by many religions simply because I had thought at one time that they had all the answers if I only found the right I'm still looking but each time I look in a different place I become a little stronger in my attitude belief if you will no faith though it's based on the evidence of past experience that I'll never find a religion which has all the Sorta like looking for Easter The more time it takes you to find the next one the more convinced you become that you may already have found all the eggs you're going to Someone else mentioned that critisism isn't going to make me think any more highly of I have a contrary position Constructive critisism will likely improve my attitude towards Abusive critisism will turn me No accusations to you I merely slipped that into this post because I forgot to reply to that Filipp Sapienza Department of Technology Services University of Michigan Hospitals Surgery Muppets and Garlic Toast Max Bob Muir PS I'm leaving for home on Thursday at so this is likely my last post here for the summer In the meantime thank you all for helping me see a few more things I might have missed in my meanderings through the world